Catonis. — in Originibus: M. Porcius Cato the Censor (234- 149 Rc.) wrote a historical work in seven books entitled Origines. The first contained the story of the Roman kings; the second and third the history of the Italian states; the fourth and fifth an account of the First and Second Punic XVars ; the sixth and seventh brought the history down to the year of Cato's death, 149 B.C.—in epulis canere: cf.
